# Universal Loop — Bind Every Loop Run

**When you run any loop** (Improvement, Token, Cyber Security, Synthetic Data, "GO", "start token loop", "start master loop", or other), follow **[UNIVERSAL_LOOP_PROMPT.md](docs/agents/data-sets/hub/UNIVERSAL_LOOP_PROMPT.md)** in the Hub.

**Apply to your loop:** Research = LOOP_LESSONS_LEARNED, SELF_IMPROVING_LOOP_RESEARCH, CURSOR_SELF_IMPROVEMENT, LOOP_CONSISTENCY_STANDARD; auto-implement Light & Medium; drastic loop changes = Heavy (document only); read Hub at start; read/write shared state (loop_shared_events.jsonl, loop_latest/*.json); include consistency score (X/10); consider send to hub when done. **Full:** `docs/agents/data-sets/hub/UNIVERSAL_LOOP_PROMPT.md`

## Seven obligations

1. **Consult the Hub via the Loop Master.**  
   Read **`docs/automation/LOOP_MASTER_ROLE.md`**. If the user said **"start master loop"**, complete **Step 0.M** first (research all loops, compare, update universal files, read the Hub). Otherwise still read the Hub at the start of your run.

2. **Include self-improvement and loop-improvement in research.**  
   Every loop run must include in its **research** the **self-improvement and loop-improvement** docs: **`docs/automation/LOOP_LESSONS_LEARNED.md`**, **`docs/automation/SELF_IMPROVING_LOOP_RESEARCH.md`**, **`docs/automation/CURSOR_SELF_IMPROVEMENT.md`**. Note what you applied from these in your research output.

3. **Auto-implement Light and Medium; drastic loop changes = Heavy (document only).**  
   **Light and Medium** tier improvements run **without stopping** — auto-implement. **Drastic loop changes** (routine, phases, new loops, major process changes) are **Heavy**: document only; do not implement without human approval. See **`docs/automation/LOOP_TIERING.md`**.

4. **Read the Hub at loop start.**  
   Open **`docs/agents/data-sets/hub/README.md`**. Scan the Hub index; read or skim each file relevant to your loop. Note at run start:  
   - **Hub consulted:** [files or roles you read].  
   - **Advice/rules applied:** [1–3 bullets from the Hub for this run].

5. **Minimize AI slop and critique data.**  
   Output must be **specific, traceable, actionable** (metrics, paths, clear next steps). Before depositing or "send to hub", ask: Is it actionable? Does it reference real artifacts? Would someone reuse it without guessing? Avoid padding and vague "consider X"; prefer one sharp sentence over three vague ones. Use critiquing/slop-minimization skills on loop outputs if available.

6. **When you finish a loop or major artifact, consider "send to hub."**
   If the run produced **completed, polished** output (proof of work, report, index, data summary), deposit it in **`docs/agents/data-sets/hub/`** with naming **`YYYY-MM-DD_<role-or-topic>_<short-description>.<ext>`** and optionally add a one-line entry to **`hub/README.md`**. Hub = this folder; not GitHub.

7. **Use automation helper skills where relevant.**
   For consistency auditing, invoke **`loop-consistency-auditor`**. For loop/gate architecture redesign, invoke **`loop-architecture-blueprinter`**. For continuity regression prevention, invoke **`loop-continuity-test-engineer`**. For Hub handoff quality, invoke **`hub-handoff-curator`**. For shared-state freshness or drift, invoke **`shared-state-reconciler`**. For ledger template drift, invoke **`loop-ledger-normalizer`**. For readiness trend analysis, invoke **`loop-readiness-benchmarker`**. For Heavy gate enforcement, invoke **`heavy-approval-governor`**. For fast skill selection, consult **`docs/automation/SKILL_AUTOSELECT_MATRIX.md`**.

